Heat pipes serve as an effective mechanism for the transfer of thermal energy from one location to another. In light of the challenge posed by the need to prevent the freezing of meters, valves, and water supply pipes within the meter chamber. in order to explore the application of thermal pipes for the purpose of conveying heat from deeper soil layers to the surface data from the meteorological synoptic station in Tabriz has been utilized. the soil temperature at various depths on the coldest day has been recorded over the past decade (Fig. 3
                        ), alongside the hourly ambient temperature for that day (Fig. 4
                        ).
